Interface CellPrintFunction

public interface CellPrintFunction
Interface with methods to create the correct String with the correct Symbols for each cell's row

Marco

  • Method Details

    • tryAddSelectionSymbols

      static java.lang.String tryAddSelectionSymbols​(java.lang.String string, SymbolsLevel selectionLevel, boolean isSelected)
      Returns String with selection Symbols at the level chosen if isSelected == true, if it isn't the methods returns the same string in input
      Parameters:
      string - original string to select
      selectionLevel - level of the selection Symbols
      isSelected - boolean parameter that set or not the selection
      Returns:
      string if isSelected == false, string between selection's level if isSelected == false

    • cellRow1

      static java.lang.String cellRow1​(java.lang.Integer blockLevel, boolean doomed, boolean thereIsWorker, ViewWorker viewWorker, boolean isSelected)
      Returns the correct String symbol in this cell's second row from up using some parameter
      Parameters:
      blockLevel - level of block's build
      doomed - boolean parameter to know if there is a dome
      thereIsWorker - boolean parameter to know if there is a worker
      viewWorker - viewWorker of worker on Cell (using only if thereIsWorker == true)
      isSelected - boolean parameter to know if the cell is selected
      Returns:
      string to string at the middle of cell's row
